knowledge_panel.description: when his cheating girlfriend leaves him, people-pleasing nice-guy gus (paul rust, "i love you, beth cooper" and "inglorious basterds") moves into a trendy apartment complex inhabited by lots of college students. a chance encounter introduces him to wild-child mickey (gillian jacobs, "community"), also recently single, and who despises her job in radio. though wildly different, the two are drawn to each other, and that relationship is the basis for the judd apatow-helmed netflix original series. and in the end, their differences may be what help them figure out just what love is.… more
